        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 26 at 9:23PM MDT until July 26 at 10:15PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>SVRGGW

The National Weather Service in Glasgow has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Phillips County in northeastern Montana...
Eastern Garfield County in northeastern Montana...
Daniels County in northeastern Montana...
Western Roosevelt County in northeastern Montana...
Valley County in northeastern Montana...
McCone County in northeastern Montana...
Northwestern Prairie County in northeastern Montana...

* Until 1015 PM MDT.

* At 922 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 21 miles east of Whitewater to near Glasgow to 9
miles west of Cohagen, moving northeast at 70 mph.

HAZARD...70 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect considerable tree damage. Damage is likely to
mobile homes, roofs, and outbuildings.

* Locations impacted include...
Glasgow, Wolf Point, Scobey, Poplar, Circle, Jordan, Opheim,
Richland, Nashua, Fort Peck, Saco, Flaxville, Duck Creek Rec Area,
Hell Creek Rec Area, Flowing Wells Rest Area, Peerless, Hinsdale,
Lustre, Port Of Scobey, and Whitetail.
</description>
        <instruction>This is a DANGEROUS SITUATION. These storms are producing wind
damage across Garfield County. SEEK SHELTER NOW inside a sturdy
structure and stay away from windows!</instruction>
